headline: 1 million-square-foot data center proposed for 141 acres in Trenton
summary: Oct. 29—A California-based real estate company has purchased 141 acres of land in the city of Trenton for a planned 1 million-square-foot data center. The company, Prologis, and the City of Trenton closed on the sale the week of Oct. 13, according to Mattie Sorrentino, Prologis' vice president of communications.
